To convert the fraction \(\frac{3}{20}\) into a decimal, you simply divide the numerator by the denominator. As stated before, performing the operation yields:  
\[ \begin{align*}
&\phantom{======}-\underline{-\\}\\
&20\,\,\big)\,20\,(\text { Bring down another }\,0 )\\
&0 \, (\text { Subtraction produces zero; bring down next digit })
\end{align*} \] Which simplifies to ```python
def FractionToDecimal(numerator, denominator):
     return Decimal(str(numerator / denominator)).quantize(Decimal('0.0'))
